The NCDC Sunday night reported 86 new COVID-19 cases in Nigeria. According the the NCDC  Lagos  recorded 70 more case, 7 in FCT, Katsina 3, Akwa Ibom 3, Jigawa 1, Bauchi 1 and Borno 1. The total figure for Nigeria  has risen to 627, the Centre said on its
Twitter handle. See the breakdown: Eighty-six new cases of #COVID19 have been reported;  70 in Lagos 7 in FCT 3 in Katsina 3 in Akwa Ibom 1 in Jigawa 1 in Bauchi 1 in Borno  As at 11:50 pm 19th April there are 627 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria.  Discharged: 170 Deaths: 21 See the tweets by NCDC especially one showing the numbers for each state below: